According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Cushion Foundation (Refillable) Market was valued at USD 1.75 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 1.90 billion in 2026 to USD 3.45 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 8.0% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing steady expansion due to rising consumer preference for eco-friendly beauty products, growing popularity of K-beauty innovations, and increasing demand for refillable cosmetic packaging that reduces environmental waste while offering convenience and cost savings.
The growing emphasis on sustainable beauty practices is transforming the cosmetics industry, with refillable cushion foundations becoming a preferred choice among environmentally conscious consumers. These products combine skincare benefits with makeup performance, offering lightweight coverage, hydration, SPF protection, and portable application in a reusable compact format. Continuous innovation in recyclable packaging materials and refill systems is encouraging both premium and mass-market brands to expand their product portfolios.
